OL,5, The governor of the Bank of England has
OL,6, defended its decision to raise interest
OL,7, rates, saying there is a "real risk" of
OL,8, soaring prices becoming "embedded".    
OL,10,FInterest rates rose to 1.75% - the     
OL,11,Fbiggest rise in 27 years - with        
OL,12,Finflation now set to hit more than 13%.
OL,14,FThe UK is forecast to fall into        
OL,15,Frecession this year, with the longest  
OL,16,Fdownturn since 2008 predicted.         
OL,18,FIncreasing interest rates is one way to
OL,19,Ftry and control inflation as it raises 
OL,20,Fborrowing costs.                       
